Description: Small handmade sub-cylindrical clay net-sinker, regular very small perforation pierced through its long side, edge of perforation is irregular, smooth surface with finger impression, lightly burnt, colour light brown, light black.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), D15, Mound β
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
